# Keep the Docker build context small and reproducible.
#
# `node_modules` and `dist` are rebuilt inside the builder stage from
# `package.json` + `pnpm-lock.yaml`, so shipping them in the context
# costs hundreds of MiB for nothing (and risks dragging stale host
# artefacts into the image). Playwright reports and test results are
# host-side e2e debris. `.env*` files would bake host-specific config
# into the image; the slice's policy is build-arg-driven env vars
# (see Dockerfile).
node_modules
dist
dist-ssr
.git
.gitignore
playwright-report
test-results
*.log
.env
.env.*

# Editor / OS clutter.
.vscode
.idea
.DS_Store

# Local-only files that should never leak into an image.
*.local
coverage
